  <main>
    <section id="privacy" class="section-light">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Privacy</div>
          <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
          <p>
            This privacy policy explains how Averdon Partners Limited (“Averdon Partners”, “we”, “us”, “our”) collects, uses and protects personal data relating to clients, candidates and visitors to our website.
          </p>
          <p>
            We are a specialist executive &amp; technical search firm focused on aviation, aerospace and complex engineering. In the course of our work we process personal data in order to provide search and related services to organisations and individuals.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-2">
          <div>
            <h3>1. Who we are</h3>
            <p>
              Averdon Partners Limited is a company registered in England &amp; Wales. For the purposes of applicable data protection law (including the UK General Data Protection Regulation and the Data Protection Act 2018), we are the controller of the personal data described in this policy.
            </p>

            <h3>2. How we obtain personal data</h3>
            <p>We collect personal data in several ways, including:</p>
            <ul class="bullet-list">
              <li>Information you provide directly via email, telephone or contact forms</li>
              <li>Details shared with us in the context of a search mandate or career discussion</li>
              <li>Information obtained from professional networking sites (such as LinkedIn), company websites and public records</li>
              <li>Referrals and introductions from clients, candidates and other contacts</li>
              <li>Basic technical information collected when you visit our website (for example, IP address and browser type)</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>3. Types of personal data we process</h3>
            <p>Depending on the context, we may process:</p>
            <ul class="bullet-list">
              <li>Contact details (name, email address, telephone number, job title, organisation)</li>
              <li>Career information (CVs, employment history, skills, qualifications, professional memberships)</li>
              <li>Mandate information (reporting lines, responsibilities, compensation ranges, location and travel requirements)</li>
              <li>Notes from conversations, interviews and meetings relevant to a search or potential opportunity</li>
              <li>Communication records (emails, messages and scheduling information)</li>
              <li>Website usage data (such as pages visited and basic analytics data)</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>4. Purposes and legal bases</h3>
            <p>We use personal data for the following purposes and on the following legal bases:</p>
            <ul class="bullet-list">
              <li><strong>Providing search and advisory services</strong> – to run search processes, assess suitability, approach potential candidates and communicate with clients and candidates (legitimate interests and, where relevant, performance of a contract).</li>
              <li><strong>Responding to enquiries</strong> – to respond to contact requests, meeting requests and general queries (legitimate interests and, where appropriate, steps taken at your request prior to entering into a contract).</li>
              <li><strong>Business development and relationship management</strong> – to maintain contact with clients, candidates and professional networks (legitimate interests).</li>
              <li><strong>Legal, regulatory and risk management</strong> – to comply with legal or regulatory obligations, exercise or defend legal claims and manage business risk (legal obligation and legitimate interests).</li>
              <li><strong>Website operation and security</strong> – to operate, maintain and secure our website and IT systems (legitimate interests and legal obligation).</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3>5. Sharing personal data</h3>
            <p>
              We only share personal data where necessary and appropriate in the context of our work. This may include sharing information with:
            </p>
            <ul class="bullet-list">
              <li>Client organisations, in connection with specific search mandates or related discussions</li>
              <li>Service providers who support our operations (for example, IT, email, document storage and communication tools)</li>
              <li>Professional advisers (for example, legal or accounting advisers) where reasonably required</li>
              <li>Regulators, law enforcement or other authorities where we are legally obliged to do so</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              We do not sell personal data to third parties.
            </p>

            <h3>6. International transfers</h3>
            <p>
              Our work may involve cross-border mandates and communications. Where personal data is transferred outside the UK or the European Economic Area, we will take appropriate steps to ensure that it is protected in accordance with applicable data protection law. This may include using standard contractual clauses or relying on an adequacy decision.
            </p>

            <h3>7. Data retention</h3>
            <p>
              We retain personal data only for as long as necessary for the purposes set out in this policy, including to satisfy legal, regulatory, accounting or reporting requirements. The precise retention period will depend on the nature of our relationship with you and the context in which the data was collected.
            </p>
            <p>
              We may retain limited contact and career information for a longer period where it remains relevant to our search work and where we have an ongoing legitimate interest in maintaining the relationship.
            </p>

            <h3>8. Your rights</h3>
            <p>
              Depending on applicable law, you may have rights in relation to your personal data, including:
            </p>
            <ul class="bullet-list">
              <li>Right of access to the personal data we hold about you</li>
              <li>Right to request correction of inaccurate or incomplete data</li>
              <li>Right to request deletion of your data in certain circumstances</li>
              <li>Right to request restriction of processing in certain circumstances</li>
              <li>Right to object to processing based on our legitimate interests</li>
              <li>Right to data portability in certain cases</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              If you wish to exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the details below. We may need to verify your identity before responding to your request.
            </p>

            <h3>9. Contact details</h3>
            <p>
              If you have any questions about this policy or how we handle personal data, please contact:
            </p>
            <ul class="bullet-list">
              <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:info@averdonpartners.com">info@averdonpartners.com</a></li>
            </ul>

            <h3>10. Updates to this policy</h3>
            <p>
              We may update this privacy policy from time to time to reflect changes in law, regulation or how we operate. Any updated version will be published on this page with an amended “last updated” date.
            </p>
            <p>
              Last updated: [insert date].
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
